That may be the best way to eliminate twinking (if you think twinking is a bad thing) but it absolutely ruins any hope of establishing an economy.  I've played on many MUDs that require a level for equipping and all it does is prevent people from trading items.  High end items become essentially &quot;sacrifices&quot; without any use whatsoever.  Degrading items is another option some MUDs choose, but that simply leads to player hassle and workarounds.  I'm not sure how bustling the trade economy on DAOC is which has both degradation and a pseudo level limit.  My hunch is there isn't a whole lot of trading relating to looted items.<br>
<br>
The biggest problem Verant has with a &quot;spreading&quot; out player base is the lack of effective cross-zone communication tools for those seeking groups/adventure/whatnot.  LFG was an attempt but because of lack of player use etc. it has not been the savior it might have been.  To improve the ease of grouping Verant needs to establish:<br>
<br>
